║  FAIRNESS & METHODOLOGY NOTES                                              ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

  COMPILER:       g++ -std=c++17 -Wall -O3 -DNDEBUG (identical for all)
  TIMING:         11 runs, drop min & max → 9 effective.
                  1 warmup run(s) (untimed) before measurement.
  STATISTICS:     Median (primary), mean, stddev, min, max, 95% CI.
                  CI: t-distribution (df=8, t=2.306).

  SCANS (v):      Nodes dequeued & settled. Should be identical across all
                  correct Dijkstra variants. Small differences = tie-breaking.

  UPDATES (i):    CRITICAL FAIRNESS CAVEAT:
    BH,4H,FH,PH,Dial,R1,R2,OMBI: count every dist[v] improvement.
    SQ (Goldberg): counts BUCKET MOVES only (bckOld != bckNew).
    SQ 'i' is LOWER and NOT directly comparable. Marked with (*).

  MEMORY:         Peak RSS via GNU /usr/bin/time -v. Includes graph storage.
                  Delta between impls = priority queue overhead.

  SCALABILITY:    Log-log regression of median time vs node count.
                  Slope ~1.0 = near-linear. Slope ~1.2 = O(n log n).

  GRAPHS:
    Road:  Real DIMACS 9th Challenge road networks (BAY/COL/FLA/NW/NE).
    Grid:  Synthetic WxW grids, uniform degree-4, random weights.
      w100    — narrow [1,100]: many bucket collisions
      w100000 — wide [1,100000]: spread across buckets
      Note: grid_3162x3162_w100000 did not complete (resource limits).

  OMBI VARIANTS:
    ombi      — Standard (ombi.cc): simpler, baseline correctness.
    ombi_opt  — Optimized: packed state, pool alloc, force-inline.
    ombi_v2   — Caliber/F-set: exact-distance vertices skip buckets.
    ombi_v3   — Two-level bitmap: fastest variant.

  SENSITIVITY:
    BW_MULT:     Bucket width = BW_MULT x minArcLen.
                 Default=4. Tested: {1,2,3,4,6,8}.
    HOT_BUCKETS: Number of hot-zone circular buckets.
                 Default=2^14 (16384). Tested: 2^10..2^18.

  CORRECTNESS:   MD5 of all source->distance checksums vs BH reference.

